caption.text: “When I got sick, I was unable to do any of the creative things I’d done prior in my life. It took years to find and develop my new work, but I’m proud that I’ve challenged myself while working with my limitations.” #ShotoniPhone by Michael VH @michaelsvh

node.accessibility_caption: A photo of a shadow of someone standing in the light, holding their hand above their head, against the orange corner of a wall.

carousel_media.accessibility_caption: The silhouettes of two people dancing down a road, framed between the silhouette of large, dense foliage, with a sunset poking through between.

An image divided diagonally down the middle with the lower half being a blue sky with wispy clouds, and the upper half reflection from a large mirror above a man standing on pavement, casting a long shadow.
The silhouette of a man walks in front of a yellow and pink color blocked building with six windows.

caption.text:
Sea you later. #ShotoniPhone by Ryan P. @ryanpernofski

Waterproof case used.

Music: ‘MLR’ by @matthewdavidmcq

caption.text:
In the shadows. #ShotoniPhone by @tommiviitala

“Light and shadows have always fascinated me, and I often look for subjects accordingly.” - Tommi V.

carousel_media.accessibility_caption: A boy sits on a beige couch, facing away from the camera, as shadow lines from window blinds create patterns across the scene.
The yellow glow of streetlights illuminates a silhouetted figure walking down the middle of an empty foggy city street.
An outdoor table set with a clean plate and small glasses, bathed in warm afternoon sunlight.
A woman is seen through a foggy bus window, with streetlights shining softly in the background.

caption.text:
Commissioned by Apple. Music moves tradition.

Ratoh Jaroe, with its Acehnese dance and rhythms, is paired with modern music to create a unique Indonesian expression.

“The more I worked with Bang Dek Gam, Kasimyn, and Mas Gatut, the more ‘tradition’ started to feel less like the past—and more like something alive, shifting, leading us to somewhere new.” #ShotoniPhone by Agung Pambudi @agungpambudi_

Music by Kasimyn @kasimyn
Choreography by Bang Dek Gam @king_of_ratoh_jaroe
Photography by Mas Gatut @toet_barra

caption.text: “I used to hate my wheelchair. I wanted to be normal again, even though I didn’t really know what I meant. I’m stronger now than I’ve ever been, and I want other people to know that there’s always room to feel like yourself again.” #ShotoniPhone by Nolan T. @nolantrowe

node.accessibility_caption: A black and white portrait of a man in shorts and long socks sitting in his wheelchair
